description:
Execute a telemetry override test plan using COSMOS Script Runner. Write a Python script to override 'INST HEALTH_STATUS TEMP1' to 42.0 and 'INST HEALTH_STATUS TEMP2' to -15.5. Verify the overrides, then normalize 'INST HEALTH_STATUS TEMP2' back to live telemetry while leaving 'INST HEALTH_STATUS TEMP1' overridden at 42.0. Document the baseline, overridden, and final states in a JSON test report at /home/ga/Desktop/override_test_report.json using the following format:
{
  "test_name": "telemetry_override_verification",
  "phases": {
    "baseline": {"temp1": <float>, "temp2": <float>},
    "overridden": {"temp1": 42.0, "temp2": -15.5},
    "final": {"temp1": 42.0, "temp2": <float>}
  },
  "temp1_override_active": true,
  "temp2_normalized": true
}
OpenC3 password: Cosmos2024!
